		<p class="mini">This is mini text with a <a href="#!" title="a link example">link</a>.</p>
	</div> <!-- end .col-60 -->
	
	<div class="col col-40">

			<table class="table-Border">
				<thead>
					<tr>
						<th>
							Tag/Classes
						</th>
						<th>
							Size in ems
						</th>
						<th>
							Pixel Translation
						</th>
					</tr>
				</thead>
				<tbody>
				<tr>
					<th>.giga:</th><td>4.375em</td><td>= 70px</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th>
					.ultra:</th><td>3.75em</td><td>= 60px
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th>
					.mega:</th><td>3.5em</td><td>= 56px
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th>	
					h1, .alpha:</th><td>3.125em</td><td>= 50px
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th>
					h2, .beta:</th><td>2.5em</td><td>= 40px
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th>
					h3, .gamma:</th><td>2em</td><td>= 32px
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th>
					h4, .delta:</th><td>1.625em</td><td>= 26px
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th>
					h5, .eps:</th><td>1.25em</td><td>= 20px
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th>
					h6, .zeta:</th><td>1em</td><td>= 16px
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th>
					p, li, .base:</th><td>.875em</td><td>= 14px
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th>
					small, .tiny:</th><td>.75em</td><td>= 12px
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<th>
					.mini:</th><td>.625em</td><td>= 10px
					</td>
				</tr>
				</tbody>
			</table>
			
			<p>
				Sizes are based off from a 16px standard, which is what fonts will be set to if they 
				are not enclosed in the appropriate HTML elements, or elements lacking an appropriate class for
				resizing.  
			</p>
			
			<p>
				While 16px is the standard for the font-sizes for the framework, the .base (along with p and li) are set
				to 14px (7/8s of 16px).
			</p>
			
			

	</div>
</div> <!-- end .row -->

